title: LockDown पर 21 दिन बाद क्या होगा ? | Modi मंत्र को समझो, 'व्रत' से मरेगा Virus |CoronavirusOutbreak
tags: Will Virus come to an end in 21 days
description:
#CoronaVirusUpdate #PMModiOnCoronaVirus #LockDownIndia
LockDown पर 21 दिन बाद क्या होगा ? | Modi मंत्र को समझो, 'व्रत' से मरेगा Virus |CoronavirusOutbreak

CoronavirusOutbreak पर अब सवाल आता है कि आखिर ये व्रत 21 दिन का ही क्यों. 21 दिन (21 days) में ऐसा क्या हो जाएगा, क्या 21 दिन में Virus का खात्मा हो जाएगा. Corona को साफ करने के लिए आखिर ये 21 दिन क्यों ज़रूरी हैं.

समझिए. इस वायरस का इनक्यूबेशन पीरियड (Virus incubation period) 14 दिन (14 days) का होता है. यानी 14 दिन के अंदर कभी भी इसके संक्रमण (Infection) का पता चल सकता है. उसके बाद 5-7 दिन तक ये दूसरों को फैला सकता है. वायरस के इस लाइफ़-साइकल (Life cycle) को ब्रेक करने के लिए सरकार ने 21 दिन का फ़ैसला लिया है.

Timane is a very easy and simple recipe. This healthy recipe is light on stomach. You can try this recipe as a healthy breakfast or evening snack too. This is Vidarbha special recipe made from only moong dal. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
• 1/2 cup Moong dal
• 2~3 chopped Green chilies
• 7~8 chopped Garlic cloves
• A little Water
• 1/4 tsp Turmeric powder
• Salt to taste
• Finely chopped Coriander leaves (Optional)
• Oil

Method:
• Wash moong dal really good 2-3 times with water. 
• Soak the dal in enough water for about 6-7 hours or overnight. 
• Transfer the soaked moong dal into a blender jar and add green chilies, garlic, water and blend 
  into smooth paste. 
• Transfer the paste into a bowl. 
• Add a little water to adjust the consistency. The batter should have pouring consistency.
• Add turmeric powder, salt and mix everything well together. 
• Add coriander leaves and mix well.
• Coriander leaves are optional. You can skip it if you don’t want. 
• Heat up a pan on medium heat. 
• Brush a little oil on it.
• Add the batter at the center of the pan and spread it evenly. 
• Spread a little oil along the edges. 
• When lower side gets nice golden color spread a little oil on the upper side of timane. 
• Flip the timane over and roast well from other side too. 
• When it is roasted well from other side too fold it and take it off the pan into a dish. 
• Timane is all ready. 
• You can have them as it is or with chutney or sauce too. 
• Another way is, spread peanut chutney, roll it and enjoy.

title: Episode 12....Peacock theme...Basic Small #Rangoli & Kolam designs | Muggulu | ముగ్గులు | रंगोली
description:
Episode 12....Peacock theme...Basic Small #Rangoli & Kolam designs | Muggulu | ముగ్గులు | रंगोली 
It is our tradition to draw kolam every day morning at the door steps.
There are many benifits of drawing kolam in front of the house.
It is auspecious and believes Godess Lakshmi enters the house if kolam is drawn.
Kolam brings lot of positive vibrations and energy to you and your home.
Draw kolam soon after you wake up and then do your prayers.
Kolam or rangoli is a part of Indian culture and transferred from generation to next generation.
This ancient art form is also called as muggulu in parts  of South India like Andhra pradesh and Telangana.
People draw different creative rangoli kolam designs using kolam powder or muggu pindi which is 
actually crushed Lime stone powder available at different parts of India.
There are different types of rangoli or kolam designs like dots kolam, sikku kolam, padi kolam, Margazhi kolam.
People draw special rangoli designs for Festivals like Sankranthi (Pongal), Diwali (Deepavali), Vijaya dasami (Dasara).
Women create deepam rangoli or kolam designs during diwali festival time, create very big and Dhanurmasam muggulu (Margazhi) for Sankranthi or Pongal festival.
It is a belief among the people that drawing muggulu infront of the house in the early morning soon after wake brings
good fortune to them and their family.
People mix rice flour to lime stone powder and prepare their own kolam powder. Muggulu can also be drawn with rice flour only.
These Beautiful and creative designs are decorated with flowers based on the occasion or festival.

title: SUKH TAN HAI ?  Gippy Grewal | Happy Raikoti | Jay K | Bal Deo | Humble Music
description:
Sukh Tan Hai ? 
Narrated By - Gippy Grewal 
Lyrics - Happy Raikoti 
Music - Jay K 



ਸੁੱਖ ਤਾਂ ਹੈ ? 
ਵਾਹਿਗੁਰੂ ਨੇ ਸਾਨੂੰ ਅਣਮੁੱਲੀਆਂ ਦਾਤਾਂ ਨਾਲ ਬਖ਼ਸ਼ਿਆ ਸੀ । 
ਤੇ ਅਸੀਂ ਜਾਣੇ-ਅਣਜਾਣੇ ਚ ਉਹਦੀ ਕਦਰ ਨੀ ਪਾਈ ।। 
ਅਸੀਂ ਹਵਾ , ਪਾਣੀ , ਧਰਤ , ਆਕਾਸ਼ , ਪਸ਼ੂ-ਪੰਛੀ ਕਿਸੇ ਨਾਲ ਵੀ ਇਨਸਾਫ ਨਹੀਂ ਕੀਤਾ , ਪਰ ਪੂਰੀ ਕਾਇਨਾਤ ਫਿਰ ਵੀ ਇਨਸਾਨ ਦਾ ਮੋਹ ਭਰਿਆ ਫਿਕਰ ਕਰਦੀ ਜਾਪ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ ।। ਸਾਡੀਆਂ ਕੁਦਰਤ ਨਾਲ ਕੀਤੀਆਂ ਹਰਕਤਾਂ ਦੇ ਬਾਵਜੂਦ ਕੁਦਰਤ ਦਾ ਹਰ ਜੀਵ-ਜੰਤੂ , ਪੇੜ-ਪੌਦਾ ਤੇ ਧਰਤ-ਆਕਾਸ਼ ਸਾਡੀ ਖ਼ੈਰ ਮੰਗਦੇ ਹੋਏ ਰੱਬ ਨੂੰ ਪੁੱਛ ਰਹੇ ਨੇ , ਸੁੱਖ ਤਾਂ ਹੈ ?

Sukh Tan Hai ?
Waheguru Ne Sanu Anmuliyan Dattan Nal Baksheya Si 
Te Asi Jane - Anjane Ch Ohdi Kadar Ni Payi. 
Asi Hawa , Paani , Dhart , Akash , Pashu - Panchi Kise Nal v Insaaf Nahi Kita , Par Puri Kayinat Fir v Insaan Da Moh Bhareya Fikar Kardi Jaap Rahi Hai
Sadiyan Kudrat Nal Kitiyan Harkatan De Bavjood Kudrat Da Har Jeev - Jantu , Perh - Pauda Te Dhart - Akash Sadi khair Mangde Hoye Rab Nu Puch Rhe Ne , Sukh Tan Hai...?
